what the general issues are.

00:16:24.291 --> 00:16:25.780
And so you'll think about it.

00:16:25.780 --> 00:16:27.919
Oh, maybe we ought
to get that-- if we

00:16:27.919 --> 00:16:29.460
want to have a
patent, maybe we ought

00:16:29.460 --> 00:16:33.830
to go talk to someone before
we take it to a demo day

00:16:33.830 --> 00:16:36.680
and blow our chances.

00:16:36.680 --> 00:16:42.125
AUDIENCE: So does public
disclosure include things

00:16:42.125 --> 00:16:46.580
like telling your peers in a lab
or telling students in a class?

00:16:46.580 --> 00:16:53.510
And also, if you
[INAUDIBLE] use an object

00:16:53.510 --> 00:16:56.975
in [INAUDIBLE]
without revealing how

00:16:56.975 --> 00:17:01.322
one goes from input to
output-- is that a disclosure?

00:17:01.322 --> 00:17:02.280
JOE HADZIMA: All right.

00:17:02.280 --> 00:17:05.260
So the question is,
is a public disclosure

00:17:05.260 --> 00:17:07.339
if you talk to your
lab mates or you do it

00:17:07.339 --> 00:17:09.690
in the confines of
an academic setting.

00:17:09.690 --> 00:17:11.650
Sort of a closed
kind of setting.

00:17:11.650 --> 00:17:14.300
And in general,
yes, but you want

00:17:14.300 --> 00:17:15.900
to be very careful about that.

00:17:15.900 --> 00:17:23.760
It's one of those facts and
circumstances type things.

00:17:23.760 --> 00:17:25.550
There is an exception
to the holding

00:17:25.550 --> 00:17:30.070
out for sale for experimental
use of something.

00:17:30.070 --> 00:17:32.700
But again, the point
here is you don't

00:17:32.700 --> 00:17:34.410
want to rely on
these after the fact.

00:17:34.410 --> 00:17:37.190
You want to, if you're planning
some activities where you think

00:17:37.190 --> 00:17:39.340
it's really important
about a patent,

00:17:39.340 --> 00:17:41.790
make sure you know what the
exact rule is at that time.

00:17:41.790 --> 00:17:44.950
Because it could change
next week with a court case.

00:17:44.950 --> 00:17:47.019
These are just red
flag type things.

00:17:47.019 --> 00:17:48.560
AUDIENCE: What about
the second half?

00:17:48.560 --> 00:17:49.935
Where if you're
demoing something

00:17:49.935 --> 00:17:53.151
but you give no indication of
what it's worth [INAUDIBLE].

00:17:53.151 --> 00:17:55.650
JOE HADZIMA: So the question
is, if you're demoing something

00:17:55.650 --> 00:17:58.024
and you don't explain how it
works, is that a disclosure.

00:17:58.024 --> 00:18:00.680
It's actually been held
that way in some cases.

00:18:00.680 --> 00:18:04.050
Where you actually couldn't
see the actual device.

00:18:04.050 --> 00:18:07.970
So again, my point
is, think about ahead

00:18:07.970 --> 00:18:11.300
of time and with
the given facts,

00:18:11.300 --> 00:18:13.580
make sure you get some good
advice before you go off

00:18:13.580 --> 00:18:17.910
and do it and then wish you had
thought about it ahead of time.

00:18:17.910 --> 00:18:18.410
OK.

00:18:18.410 --> 00:18:21.510
So let me keep moving.

