Oops, let's see.

00:18:26.850 --> 00:18:28.990
Same issue from a
business plan viewpoint.

00:18:28.990 --> 00:18:30.570
Do you actually
own the technology.

00:18:30.570 --> 00:18:35.660
So a patent issues in
the name of an inventor.

00:18:35.660 --> 00:18:39.012
And a company only gets it
if the inventor assigns it.

00:18:39.012 --> 00:18:41.470
So if you're a technical person,
you go work for a company,

00:18:41.470 --> 00:18:43.660
you probably end up signing
an invention disclosure

00:18:43.660 --> 00:18:45.890
agreement and an assignment.

00:18:45.890 --> 00:18:48.980
So if you invent something
in the course of your work,

00:18:48.980 --> 00:18:50.657
you agree the employer owns it.

00:18:50.657 --> 00:18:52.490
And if you're a startup
and you hire people,

00:18:52.490 --> 00:18:55.632
you want to have something
along those lines also.

00:18:55.632 --> 00:18:57.340
You could in-license
from the university.

