00:19:09.620 --> 00:19:10.170
OK.

00:19:10.170 --> 00:19:12.980
Now obtaining a patent
involves sort of four steps.

00:19:12.980 --> 00:19:15.460
In Determining what to patent.

00:19:15.460 --> 00:19:16.970
Determining when to file.

00:19:16.970 --> 00:19:18.490
You got to prepare
the applications.

00:19:18.490 --> 00:19:20.670
And then you've got
to prosecute it,

00:19:20.670 --> 00:19:24.120
which means you negotiate
with the Patent Office

00:19:24.120 --> 00:19:25.462
about getting a patent.

00:19:25.462 --> 00:19:26.795
And that can take several years.

00:19:29.360 --> 00:19:32.650
Determining what the patent
really is more about not

00:19:32.650 --> 00:19:34.540
what can I get a patent on.

00:19:34.540 --> 00:19:35.600
Its what's useful.

00:19:35.600 --> 00:19:38.660
Because patents are
pretty expensive.

00:19:38.660 --> 00:19:41.270
And you probably don't
have enough money

00:19:41.270 --> 00:19:44.614
to patent everything
you actually invent.

00:19:44.614 --> 00:19:46.780
And when you say, what do
I want to get a patent on,

00:19:46.780 --> 00:19:48.250
you say, well, what
value does it add.

00:19:48.250 --> 00:19:50.624
Remember we talked about we
want to create value-- that's

00:19:50.624 --> 00:19:53.000
part of the mission here.

00:19:53.000 --> 00:19:54.410
If I patent this,
is it valuable.

00:19:54.410 --> 00:19:55.910
Does it create commercial value.

00:19:55.910 --> 00:20:00.410
Does it prevent
competitors from using it.

00:20:00.410 --> 00:20:03.082
And in determining whether
it has commercial value

00:20:03.082 --> 00:20:05.290
or not, or whether you can
easily get a patent on it,

00:20:05.290 --> 00:20:08.602
you want to compare
against the prior art.

00:20:08.602 --> 00:20:11.060
So this is where I get to do
a little pitch for the company

00:20:11.060 --> 00:20:13.660
that I founded called IP Vision.

00:20:13.660 --> 00:20:16.630
We were doing early stage
technology commercialization

00:20:16.630 --> 00:20:17.810
out of MIT.

00:20:17.810 --> 00:20:20.850
And the problem we had doing
the same kind of things

00:20:20.850 --> 00:20:24.340
we're talking about
in class-- market,

00:20:24.340 --> 00:20:26.525
time to market, what's the
strategy-- is we always

00:20:26.525 --> 00:20:27.900
had a problem
figuring out what's

00:20:27.900 --> 00:20:29.602
the intellectual property.

00:20:29.602 --> 00:20:31.185
And the only way we
could really do it

00:20:31.185 --> 00:20:34.720
was try to read a ton of patents
or send it out to a law firm.

00:20:34.720 --> 00:20:36.580
And we get back a
