01:05:38.470 --> 01:05:41.380
Traditionally this bridged
from one round to another

01:05:41.380 --> 01:05:44.440
as you were trying to
keep the company going.

01:05:44.440 --> 01:05:49.550
It has the benefit of being
quick, relatively inexpensive,

01:05:49.550 --> 01:05:52.530
and it can avoid
valuation issues.

01:05:52.530 --> 01:05:55.240
So a classic problem
is the first run

01:05:55.240 --> 01:05:58.340
investors value the
company too high.

01:05:58.340 --> 01:05:59.789
The next round
comes in and says,

01:05:59.789 --> 01:06:01.830
we're never going to pay
that much because things

01:06:01.830 --> 01:06:03.620
have happened or whatever.

01:06:03.620 --> 01:06:06.390
And the first round has to
have this discussion-- how

01:06:06.390 --> 01:06:09.490
they get crammed down in their
percentage of the company.

01:06:09.490 --> 01:06:11.830
Convertible note allows
you to sort of not

01:06:11.830 --> 01:06:14.705
set that actual
valuation until later.

01:06:14.705 --> 01:06:16.080
There's a good
